---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About Jain Diet" description="Learn about Jain dietary guidelines and why certain foods are avoided">
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mb-3">About the Jain Diet</h1>
      <div class="mandala-divider justify-center max-w-xs mx-auto">
        <span class="text-gold text-xl">✦</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-warm-gray mt-4 text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Understanding the principles behind Jain vegetarian cooking
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Core Principle -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-maroon to-maroon-light text-cream rounded-3xl p-8 sm:p-12 mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-gold-light">The Principle of Ahimsa</h2>
      <p class="text-cream/85 leading-relaxed text-lg">
        Jain dietary practices are rooted in <strong class="text-cream">Ahimsa</strong> (non-violence) — the
        fundamental principle of Jain philosophy. The goal is to minimize harm to all living beings,
        including the tiniest organisms. This extends to the food we eat, how it's prepared, and
        when it's consumed.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Why Root Vegetables Are Avoided -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-3xl p-8 sm:p-10 shadow-sm mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">🚫</span>
        Why Root Vegetables Are Avoided
      </h2>
      <p class="text-warm-gray leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Uprooting a plant destroys the entire organism and the countless microorganisms living
        in the soil around its roots. Jain philosophy considers this a form of violence. Root
        vegetables also have the potential to sprout new life — consuming them prevents that possibility.
      </p>
      <p class="text-warm-gray leading-relaxed">
        Additionally, root vegetables are classified as <strong>Ananthkay</strong> — organisms
        with infinite lives in a single body. Each root vegetable is considered to contain
        countless individual life forms, making their consumption particularly harmful from
        a Jain perspective.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- What's Avoided vs. Allowed -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-10">
      <!-- Not Allowed -->
      <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-100 rounded-3xl p-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-800 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-2xl">❌</span> Not Allowed
        </h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          {[
            { name: 'Onion', note: 'Root vegetable, pungent' },
            { name: 'Garlic', note: 'Root vegetable, tamasic' },
            { name: 'Potato', note: 'Root tuber' },
            { name: 'Ginger', note: 'Rhizome (underground stem)' },
            { name: 'Carrot', note: 'Root vegetable' },
            { name: 'Radish', note: 'Root vegetable' },
            { name: 'Beetroot', note: 'Root vegetable' },
            { name: 'Turnip', note: 'Root vegetable' },
            { name: 'Sweet Potato', note: 'Root tuber' },
            { name: 'Yam', note: 'Root tuber' },
            { name: 'Shallots & Leeks', note: 'Allium family' },
          ].map((item) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm">
              <span class="text-red-400 mt-0.5">●</span>
              <div>
                <strong class="text-red-800">{item.name}</strong>
                <span class="text-red-600/70 ml-1">— {item.note}</span>
              </div>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Allowed -->
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-100 rounded-3xl p-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-800 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-2xl">✅</span> Allowed
        </h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          {[
            { name: 'Paneer & Dairy', note: 'Milk, curd, ghee, butter' },
            { name: 'All Lentils & Dals', note: 'Toor, moong, chana, masoor' },
            { name: 'Above-Ground Vegetables', note: 'Cauliflower, capsicum, peas, beans' },
            { name: 'Gourds', note: 'Bottle gourd, ridge gourd, bitter gourd' },
            { name: 'Leafy Greens', note: 'Spinach, fenugreek, coriander' },
            { name: 'Brinjal (Eggplant)', note: 'Fruit vegetable' },
            { name: 'Tomato', note: 'Fruit vegetable' },
            { name: 'Grains & Rice', note: 'Wheat, rice, bajra, jowar' },
            { name: 'Dry Fruits & Nuts', note: 'Almonds, cashews, raisins' },
            { name: 'All Spices', note: 'Cumin, turmeric, coriander, pepper' },
            { name: 'Asafoetida (Hing)', note: 'Great onion/garlic substitute!' },
          ].map((item) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm">
              <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">●</span>
              <div>
                <strong class="text-green-800">{item.name}</strong>
                <span class="text-green-700/70 ml-1">— {item.note}</span>
              </div>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Paryushana Note -->
    <div class="bg-gold/5 border border-gold/20 rounded-3xl p-8 sm:p-10 mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">🪷</span>
        Paryushana & Special Fasting
      </h2>
      <p class="text-warm-gray leading-relaxed mb-4">
        During <strong>Paryushana</strong> (the most important Jain festival, lasting 8-10 days),
        many Jains observe even stricter dietary rules:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-warm-gray text-sm">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-gold mt-0.5">●</span>
          <span>Avoiding leafy green vegetables (to protect tiny insects)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-gold mt-0.5">●</span>
          <span>Not eating after sunset (to avoid harming nocturnal organisms)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-gold mt-0.5">●</span>
          <span>Some observe complete fasts or eat only once a day</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-gold mt-0.5">●</span>
          <span>Avoiding multi-seeded fruits like figs and eggplant</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Cooking Tips -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-3xl p-8 sm:p-10 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">💡</span>
        Tips for Jain Cooking
      </h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-maroon mb-2">Replacing Onion & Garlic</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-warm-gray leading-relaxed">
            Use <strong>asafoetida (hing)</strong> for a similar pungent flavor. A tiny pinch
            in hot oil mimics the depth that onion and garlic provide. Green chilies and
            cumin seeds also add flavor complexity.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-maroon mb-2">Replacing Potato</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-warm-gray leading-relaxed">
            Use <strong>raw banana (plantain)</strong>, <strong>colocasia (arbi)</strong> — wait,
            that's a root! Use <strong>paneer</strong>, <strong>bread cubes</strong>, or
            <strong>sabudana</strong> for a starchy, filling substitute.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-maroon mb-2">Replacing Ginger</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-warm-gray leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Dry ginger powder (saunth)</strong> — wait, still ginger! Use
            <strong>black pepper</strong>, <strong>cinnamon</strong>, or
            <strong>cardamom</strong> for warmth and spice.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-maroon mb-2">Building Flavor Without Roots</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-warm-gray leading-relaxed">
            Rely on <strong>tempering (tadka/vaghaar)</strong> with cumin, mustard seeds,
            curry leaves, and hing. <strong>Tomato puree</strong>, <strong>cashew paste</strong>,
            and <strong>poppy seed paste</strong> create rich gravies.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Jai Jinendra -->
    <div class="text-center mt-12">
      <span class="text-5xl block mb-3">🙏</span>
      <p class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-maroon">Jai Jinendra!</p>
      <p class="text-warm-gray mt-2">May every meal be an act of compassion.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
